---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import MetaballButton from '../components/MetaballButton.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Resonance.ID — Your brand, in one dashboard · €247"
  description="A complete brand identity delivered as a personal dashboard. Answer 12 questions, the system listens, seven modules land in your inbox the same day. €247."
>

<!-- ── HERO ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="s-hero">
  <div class="hero-body">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow r">// RESONANCE.ID — €247</p>
    <h1 class="hero-h1 diag-h">
      <span class="diag-line">Your brand,</span>
      <span class="diag-line">written back to you,</span>
      <span class="diag-line">in one evening.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-sub r" data-d="1">A complete brand identity, delivered as a personal, password-protected dashboard. You answer 12 questions. The system listens. Seven modules land in your inbox the same day.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas r" data-d="2">
      <MetaballButton href="mailto:saja@resonance-os.studio?subject=Start%20my%20Resonance.ID" label="Start your ID — €247" />
      <MetaballButton href="/site" variant="ghost" label="Or see Resonance.SITE" />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ── LOGO SEPARATOR ────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="logo-sep" aria-hidden="true">
  <svg class="logo-sep-mark" viewBox="0 0 550 550" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <use href="#logo-mark"/>
  </svg>
</div>


<!-- ── WHAT IT IS ───────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="s" id="overview">
  <span class="lbl r">// WHAT YOU GET</span>
  <h2 class="h2 diag-h r" data-d="1">
    <span class="diag-line">Seven modules.</span>
    <span class="diag-line">One dashboard.</span>
  </h2>

  <div class="prod-grid">
    <div class="r" data-d="2">
      <p class="body" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem">Resonance.ID is a complete brand identity, delivered as a personal, password-protected dashboard. Seven modules — written from your intake answers, set in your typography, painted in your palette.</p>
      <ol class="mod-list">
        <li class="mod-item"><span class="mod-n">01 ·</span> Who you are — written back to you, in your own words</li>
        <li class="mod-item"><span class="mod-n">02 ·</span> Why you do this — the honest root</li>
        <li class="mod-item"><span class="mod-n">03 ·</span> Who you're for, who you're not</li>
        <li class="mod-item"><span class="mod-n">04 ·</span> How you look — palette, typography, atmosphere</li>
        <li class="mod-item"><span class="mod-n">05 ·</span> How you sound — voice rules, worked examples</li>
        <li class="mod-item"><span class="mod-n">06 ·</span> How your website should work — section blueprint</li>
        <li class="mod-item"><span class="mod-n">07 ·</span> How you summarize yourself — five taglines, one recommended</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="price-note">€247 · Generated within 30 seconds · Sent to your inbox the same day.</p>
      <MetaballButton href="mailto:saja@resonance-os.studio?subject=Start%20my%20Resonance.ID" label="Start your ID" />
    </div>

    <aside class="vault-card r" data-d="3">
      <header class="vault-card-hd">
        <span class="vault-card-eyebrow">// Resonance.ID · Brand Vault</span>
        <span class="vault-card-status">Live</span>
      </header>
      <div class="vault-card-swatches" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="vault-card-sw" style="background:#f9f9f9"></span>
        <span class="vault-card-sw" style="background:#f0eee9"></span>
        <span class="vault-card-sw" style="background:#d4cfc9"></span>
        <span class="vault-card-sw" style="background:#f75b1d"></span>
        <span class="vault-card-sw" style="background:#222222"></span>
      </div>
      <hr class="vault-card-divider" />
      <p class="vault-card-section">// Recommended tagline</p>
      <blockquote class="vault-card-quote">"Where your body finds its frequency."</blockquote>
      <p class="vault-card-why">Fits both studio and product narratives — recommended by the system.</p>
      <footer class="vault-card-foot">
        <span>7 modules</span><span class="sep">·</span>
        <span>Aa Urbanist</span><span class="sep">·</span>
        <span>#F75B1D</span><span class="sep">·</span>
        <span>ID System v3</span>
      </footer>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ── HOW IT WORKS ─────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="s" id="how" style="background:var(--bg-alt)">
  <span class="lbl r">// HOW IT WORKS</span>
  <h2 class="h2 diag-h r" data-d="1">
    <span class="diag-line">Three steps.</span>
    <span class="diag-line">About 20 minutes.</span>
  </h2>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step r" data-d="1">
      <span class="step-n">01</span>
      <p class="step-h">You answer 12 questions.</p>
      <p class="step-p">Not a corporate form. A conversation, in your own words. About 20 minutes. What you do, how you teach, who you're for — and what you're tired of saying about yourself that still doesn't land.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="step r" data-d="2">
      <span class="step-n">02</span>
      <p class="step-h">The system listens.</p>
      <p class="step-p">It reads where your energy went. It does not paraphrase what was already strong. Your literal words, where they're strongest, end up in the output. That's the whole mechanism.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="step r" data-d="3">
      <span class="step-n">03</span>
      <p class="step-h">Your dashboard is generated.</p>
      <p class="step-p">Within 30 seconds. Sent to your inbox with a private link and access code. Then a 20-minute walk-through with Saja — to make sure it actually sits right.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ── WHO IT'S FOR ─────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="s" id="who">
  <span class="lbl r">// WHO IT'S FOR</span>
  <h2 class="h2 diag-h r" data-d="1">
    <span class="diag-line">This is built</span>
    <span class="diag-line">for one kind</span>
    <span class="diag-line">of person.</span>
  </h2>
  <div class="who-grid">
    <div class="r" data-d="2">
      <p class="who-col-ttl">For you if</p>
      <ul class="who-list">
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot">●</span>You run a boutique studio or work 1-on-1</li>
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot">●</span>You've been at it three years or more</li>
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot">●</span>You're at a turning point — repositioning, expanding, raising your prices, going online</li>
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot">●</span>Your Instagram looks like you. Your website doesn't.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="r" data-d="3">
      <p class="who-col-ttl">Not for you if</p>
      <ul class="who-list">
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot" style="color:var(--ink-m)">●</span>You run a franchise</li>
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot" style="color:var(--ink-m)">●</span>You started this year</li>
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot" style="color:var(--ink-m)">●</span>You sell drop-in only</li>
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot" style="color:var(--ink-m)">●</span>You're shopping for a logo</li>
        <li class="who-item"><span class="who-dot" style="color:var(--ink-m)">●</span>You're not in movement, wellness, or somatic work</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ── WHAT YOU WALK AWAY WITH ─────────────────────── -->
<section class="s" id="sample" style="background:var(--bg-alt)">
  <span class="lbl r">// WHAT YOU WALK AWAY WITH</span>
  <h2 class="h2 diag-h r" data-d="1">
    <span class="diag-line">A live preview</span>
    <span class="diag-line">of what €247</span>
    <span class="diag-line">gets you.</span>
  </h2>
  <div class="vault-full r" data-d="2">
    <div class="vault-full-hd">
      <span class="vault-full-ttl">Resonance.ID — Anonymous Preview · All seven modules</span>
      <div class="swatches" style="margin-bottom:0">
        <div class="sw" style="background:#f9f9f9"></div>
        <div class="sw" style="background:#f0eee9"></div>
        <div class="sw" style="background:#f75b1d"></div>
        <div class="sw" style="background:#222222"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="vault-modules">
      <div class="vmod"><p class="vmod-n">01</p><p class="vmod-ttl">Who you are</p><p class="vmod-sub">Written back to you, in your own words — not paraphrased, not sanitized.</p></div>
      <div class="vmod"><p class="vmod-n">02</p><p class="vmod-ttl">Why you do this</p><p class="vmod-sub">The honest root. The thing that was true before the business existed.</p></div>
      <div class="vmod"><p class="vmod-n">03</p><p class="vmod-ttl">Who you're for</p><p class="vmod-sub">Your person, exactly. And the person who would waste your time.</p></div>
      <div class="vmod"><p class="vmod-n">04</p><p class="vmod-ttl">How you look</p><p class="vmod-sub">Palette, typography, atmosphere — and the rules that hold them together.</p></div>
      <div class="vmod"><p class="vmod-n">05</p><p class="vmod-ttl">How you sound</p><p class="vmod-sub">Voice rules with worked examples. What to say. What to stop saying.</p></div>
      <div class="vmod"><p class="vmod-n">06</p><p class="vmod-ttl">How your website should work</p><p class="vmod-sub">Section-by-section blueprint. What goes where. What to cut.</p></div>
      <div class="vmod vmod--acc"><p class="vmod-n">07</p><p class="vmod-ttl">How you summarize yourself</p><p class="vmod-sub">Five taglines. One recommended — with a note on why that one.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ── FAQ ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="s" id="faq">
  <span class="lbl r">// FAQ</span>
  <h2 class="h2 diag-h r" data-d="1" style="margin-bottom:0">
    <span class="diag-line">Common questions.</span>
  </h2>
  <div class="faq-grid">
    <div class="faq-col">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-q">Do I need a logo first?<svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M7 1v12M1 7h12"/></svg></summary>
        <p class="faq-a">No. Resonance.ID produces the brief that tells a designer what to build. You can commission a logo after, hand the ID to your own designer, or come back for Resonance.SITE. The ID comes first because the logo should come from the brand — not the other way around.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-q">What if my answers come out messy?<svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M7 1v12M1 7h12"/></svg></summary>
        <p class="faq-a">That's fine. The system is reading for where your energy went, not for polish. Messy answers often produce the strongest output because the real thing slips out before you can tidy it up.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-q">Can I use Resonance.ID without buying a website?<svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M7 1v12M1 7h12"/></svg></summary>
        <p class="faq-a">Yes. Most people do. The ID is a complete, standalone brand document. You can hand it to your own developer or designer, use it to brief a copywriter, or just use it as a reference when you write your own copy.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-col">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-q">What if I already have a designer?<svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M7 1v12M1 7h12"/></svg></summary>
        <p class="faq-a">Your designer will love you for it. Resonance.ID is a design brief. Most designers spend weeks extracting exactly this information from clients. You'll arrive at their door with it already done.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-q">Does it work in Dutch?<svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M7 1v12M1 7h12"/></svg></summary>
        <p class="faq-a">Yes. Answer in Dutch, get your ID in Dutch. The system reads the language you write in and outputs in the same language. If you want the output in English, answer in English.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-q">What if the output doesn't feel right?<svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M7 1v12M1 7h12"/></svg></summary>
        <p class="faq-a">That's what the walk-through is for. Every Resonance.ID includes a 20-minute session with Saja. If the tagline is close but not quite right, we adjust it live. If a module missed the mark, we talk through why and fix it.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Base>
